args:
The passion of the bon dance helps Catherine
and Eugene clear up their ill feelings, which
warms the hearts of the Styxes and makes them
transform into their mature form. Sadly, the pair
realizes this will mean being parted from Sam,
and prepares to bid a reluctant farewell.
We're back from taking down the fiends.
The passion and heat of this dance is\neven impressing a fire dragon like me!
Okay, this is weird. I feel all...hot.
And I as wellâ€”to think it all comes from\nus performing the same movements!
I can feel her movements!\nHer consciousness!
As rocs are set against the merles,\nso too is it the same as they swim\nthrough the eddies of passion.
Each who dances is their own.\nThough miles apart, they're yet alike.
All are fools together in perfect harmony.\nAnd in this, we have the dance of Bon!
When I attended my first school,\nI realized something.
There's two kinds of people in the world:
People who can talk well...\nand people who can't.
People who can laugh along,\nand people who can't.
All I do is cower in the dark.
That was the birthday party I was\ninvited to by a school friend.
I realized how others viewed me.
The mayor's daughter. A wealthy child.
A girl with vast advantages.\nA girl who could be used.
The idea that people would view me for\nwho I really was was a mere fantasy.
Listen, I can manage anything perfectly.
In fact, I'M the one who rejected THEM.
Trying just means getting worn out.
If I hold out my hand,\nwill something change?
Would it be easier if I gave up?
You're always at the center of everything.
You always stand apart from everyone.
I'm miserable when I look at you.
I feel so foolish when I look at you.
Looks like you woke up, Eugene.
Ensnared in passions. Lost in the dream.\nAh, and the young lady seems to be\nwaking as well.
Hey, so, um...do you maybe wanna...\ncome play board games at my place\nsometime? I mean...Sam'll be there.

It's got nothing to do with whose daughter
you are! It's just that when you're around
we can both...you know? Relax or just be
sort of... Rrrgh! This is hard!
Perhaps it would be good to enjoy a\nbit of leisure time and some nougat.
Thank you, Eugene. I don't think I've ever\nhad such a sincere invitation in my life.
Now THAT is what I call a reconciliation.
Correct. There can be no mischief with\nthis much passion in two hearts.\nThe hour for trouble has passed on.
Whoa! The Styxes combined into one!
This is Styx's mature form. She has\naccepted Catherine and Eugene's growth,\nand so has grown up as well.
Sam and the mature form you see there\nwere originally one, and they are returning\nto that state now.
Wait. Sam and that dragon are one?\nHa ha! Maybe they'll both come over\nand play board games!

Styx is the guardian dragon of great rivers.
The immature version appears before
people to evaluate if they are worthy
of receiving blessings.
If so, she grows into her mature form and\nreturns to the river. Then she works to\nbring about the blessing of water to all.
But she loses her memories from her\nimmature form, and is left with only\na base affection towards people.
Oh no! Does that mean...\nwe have to say goodbye to Sam?
Styx has repeated this cycle since ancient\ntimes. It is her nature, her providence.\nThere can be no exception.
Clear waters of the great rivers ascend to\nthe skies, become clouds, then fall back\nto the land as rain.
Though they make one equally damp,\ntears and rain are yet a world apart.\nSpare not your smiles; see your friend off.
You are both...friends.\nWhen you are friends...I am happy.
Sam did all of this in order\nto bring blessings to everyone.
